extendedInfo.description: Babozoo is the Perfect Game from the Age of 6 Months. Let Baby Explore Over Fifty Different Animals Cartoons and Calls.Baby decides the rhythm of run of the images and this dynamics stimulates its cognitive development. In a coloured and sound environment, your baby will develop his visual and auditive memory. It is a play which implies really the child, it is amusing and full with surprises. It makes more than to satisfy the curiosity of the young children, it develops a true pleasure of learning.

reviews.title: Needs a lock.
reviews.comment: Really good game. Captivates my 9 month old so well. He loves it! It really needs a way to lock it into the game, though. It\'s too easy to exit the game and do all sorts of things I don\'t want a 9 month old doing. Would get 5 stars if it had a lock.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Awesome!
reviews.comment: My son had loved this app since he was 4mos, now he\'s about to turn 1 and it is still his favorite! All of the animal sounds are very accurate, except for the weird random singing mouse. Doesn\'t lock, but I got a kids app folder that does lock so when he exits, he can only go into baby apps I put in it. Problem solved, thus 5 stars.
reviews.author: Cara Dennis

reviews.comment: My daughter loves this game. BUT it needs a lock. Like the home key is disabled and the back key has to be double pressed then a short code typed in. Please put a lock!
reviews.author: Amanda Ngiraibiochel

reviews.title: Brilliant!
reviews.comment: This app has captivated my 5 1/2 month old since he was 3-4 months old. He loves the moving animal faces and has even started to mimic their sounds! The best part is that the animals keep changing on their own so I dont have to keep pressing anything. Stops him for crying in an instant & gives me time to get things done!! We need more apps like this!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: 1 year old still loves this app
reviews.comment: I got this app quite awhile ago for my daughter and she figured out right away how to get a new animal up and would quickly get excited when I let her play with it. Months later she gets just as excited about it. It keeps her entertained every time! She does get out of the game so a lock would be ideal! (that would get it 5 stars!)
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Love but wish it locked the phone
reviews.comment: My daughter loves this app since like 8 months.   Problem is it doesn\'t lock your phone and she can easily hit the home key and get out the app then she starts crying.  Wish it locked all keys like toddler lock app.
